1
02:29:14,917 --> 02:29:16,585
BILBO: Can you see anything?
OIN [WHISPERING]: Shh! Keep it down.

2
02:29:16,835 --> 02:29:19,797
THORIN [WHISPERING]: As soon as we have the
weapons, we make straight for the mountain.

3
02:29:20,047 --> 02:29:21,215
GO, go!

4
02:29:21,632 --> 02:29:22,799
DORI [WHISPERING]:
Go, Nori.

5
02:29:25,928 --> 02:29:26,929
Next.

6
02:29:40,234 --> 02:29:41,401
You all right?

7
02:29:41,652 --> 02:29:42,945
I can manage.

8
02:29:43,695 --> 02:29:45,280
Let's just get out of here.

9
02:29:47,699 --> 02:29:48,700
[GRUNTS]

10
02:29:51,662 --> 02:29:53,080
[WEAPONS CLATTERING]

11
02:29:56,083 --> 02:29:57,543
[GUARDS SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]

12
02:29:59,294 --> 02:30:00,170
Run!

13
02:30:00,420 --> 02:30:01,547
GLOIN:
Quickly! Move now!

14
02:30:03,298 --> 02:30:03,882
[GRUNTS]

15
02:30:04,591 --> 02:30:05,509
[YELLING]

16
02:30:15,686 --> 02:30:16,895
Get off me! Get off!

17
02:30:17,145 --> 02:30:18,730
GUARD:
Move them along here.

18
02:30:19,856 --> 02:30:20,857
BRAGA:
Move on!

19
02:30:29,491 --> 02:30:30,951
What is the meaning of this?

20
02:30:31,952 --> 02:30:34,288
BRAGA: We caught them stealing weapons, sire.
MASTER: Ah.

21
02:30:34,788 --> 02:30:36,832
Enemies of the state, eh?

22
02:30:37,082 --> 02:30:37,875
ALFRID:
A desperate bunch of...

23
02:30:38,125 --> 02:30:40,294
...mercenaries, if ever there was, sire.

24
02:30:40,544 --> 02:30:41,753
Hold your tongue!

25
02:30:44,381 --> 02:30:46,466
You do not know to whom you speak.

26
02:30:47,050 --> 02:30:48,927
This is no common criminal.

27
02:30:49,219 --> 02:30:50,554
This is Thorin...

28
02:30:50,804 --> 02:30:53,932
...son of Thrain, son of Thror!

29
02:30:55,183 --> 02:30:56,643
[CROWD MURMURING]

30
02:30:57,102 --> 02:30:59,187
We are the Dwarves of Erebor.

31
02:31:01,899 --> 02:31:05,068
We have come to reclaim our homeland.

32
02:31:09,781 --> 02:31:12,784
I remember this town
in the great days of old.

33
02:31:14,077 --> 02:31:16,121
Fleets of boats lay at harbor...

34
02:31:16,371 --> 02:31:17,789
...filled with silks and fine gems.

35
02:31:19,166 --> 02:31:21,376
This was no forsaken town on a lake.

36
02:31:22,419 --> 02:31:25,088
This was the center of all trade
in the North!

37
02:31:26,923 --> 02:31:27,507
I would...

38
02:31:27,758 --> 02:31:28,967
...see those days return.

39
02:31:29,217 --> 02:31:31,720
I would relight the great forges
of the Dwarves...

40
02:31:31,970 --> 02:31:32,930
...and send wealth and riches...

41
02:31:33,180 --> 02:31:35,641
...flowing once more
from the Halls of Erebor!

42
02:31:35,891 --> 02:31:36,975
[CHEERING]

43
02:31:38,644 --> 02:31:39,227
BARD:
Death!

44
02:31:40,437 --> 02:31:41,438
That is what you will...

45
02:31:41,688 --> 02:31:42,981
...bring upon us!

46
02:31:43,857 --> 02:31:45,525
Dragon fire and ruin.

47
02:31:48,028 --> 02:31:49,905
If you waken that beast...

48
02:31:50,530 --> 02:31:52,115
...it will destroy us all.

49
02:31:52,366 --> 02:31:54,201
THORIN:
You can listen to this naysayer...

50
02:31:54,451 --> 02:31:56,078
...but I promise you this:

51
02:31:58,497 --> 02:31:59,915
If we succeed...

52
02:32:01,291 --> 02:32:03,794
...all will share in the wealth
of the mountain.

53
02:32:04,044 --> 02:32:05,337
[CROWD CHATTERING]

54
02:32:08,215 --> 02:32:11,259
You will have enough gold
to rebuild Esgaroth...

55
02:32:11,510 --> 02:32:12,719
...10 times over!

56
02:32:12,970 --> 02:32:14,262
[CROWD CHEERS]

57
02:32:14,763 --> 02:32:15,931
All of you!

58
02:32:16,264 --> 02:32:17,391
Listen to me!

59
02:32:17,641 --> 02:32:18,684
You must listen!

60
02:32:18,934 --> 02:32:20,644
Have you forgotten
what happened to Dale?

61
02:32:22,479 --> 02:32:23,397
Have you forgotten those...

62
02:32:23,647 --> 02:32:25,691
...who died in the firestorm?!

63
02:32:27,985 --> 02:32:28,902
And for what purpose?

64
02:32:30,404 --> 02:32:32,197
The blind ambition of a Mountain King...

65
02:32:33,073 --> 02:32:35,075
...so riven by greed, he could not...

66
02:32:35,325 --> 02:32:36,827
...see beyond his own desire!

67
02:32:38,078 --> 02:32:39,705
MASTER:
Now, now!

68
02:32:39,997 --> 02:32:41,957
We must not, any of us...

69
02:32:42,207 --> 02:32:44,584
...be too quick to lay blame.

70
02:32:45,711 --> 02:32:46,294
Let us...

71
02:32:46,545 --> 02:32:48,255
...not forget that it was...

72
02:32:48,505 --> 02:32:50,298
...Girion, Lord of Dale...

73
02:32:50,549 --> 02:32:52,217
...your ancestor...

74
02:32:52,467 --> 02:32:54,970
...who failed to kill the beast!

75
02:32:57,514 --> 02:32:59,474
ALFRID:
It's true, sire.

76
02:32:59,725 --> 02:33:00,934
We all know the story.

77
02:33:02,519 --> 02:33:04,187
Arrow after arrow, he shot.

78
02:33:04,438 --> 02:33:07,024
Each one missing its mark.

79
02:33:13,780 --> 02:33:15,032
You have no right.

80
02:33:16,742 --> 02:33:18,660
No right to enter that mountain.

81
02:33:20,370 --> 02:33:22,497
I have the only right.

82
02:33:28,837 --> 02:33:30,213
I speak to the Master...

83
02:33:30,464 --> 02:33:31,923
...of the Men of the Lake.

84
02:33:32,174 --> 02:33:34,468
Will you see the prophecy fulfilled?

85
02:33:35,427 --> 02:33:36,386
Will you...

86
02:33:36,762 --> 02:33:40,515
...share in the great wealth
of our people?

87
02:33:45,520 --> 02:33:46,980
What say you?

88
02:33:50,859 --> 02:33:53,904
I say unto you...

89
02:33:55,155 --> 02:33:56,156
Welcome!

90
02:33:56,698 --> 02:33:57,365
Welcome!

91
02:33:57,741 --> 02:33:58,700
And thrice...

92
02:33:58,950 --> 02:33:59,951
...welcome...

93
02:34:00,202 --> 02:34:01,828
...King Under the Mountain!

